ark">✓</span>COMMON WORKPLACE BIASES</div><div class="nav-item" id="nav-bias_impact" onclick="showSection('bias_impact')"><span class="checkmark">✓</span>HOW BIAS AFFECTS DECISIONS</div><div class="nav-item" id="nav-quiz" onclick="showSection('quiz')"><span class="checkmark">✓</span>BIAS RECOGNITION QUIZ</div><div class="nav-item" id="nav-summary" onclick="showSection('summary')"><span class="checkmark">✓</span>SUMMARY & REFLECTION</div></div></div><div class="content-container"><div class="content-header"><div class="mobile-menu-btn" onclick="toggleMobileMenu()">☰</div><div class="content-title"><h1>INCLUSIVE LEADERSHIP - PRE-WORK</h1><div class="lesson-info">Module 4 of 12</div><h2>UNDERSTANDING UNCONSCIOUS BIAS AT WORK</h2></div><div class="logo-placeholder"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/9FkZdTvQ/taa-circles-only-no-TAA-png.png" alt="Logo"></div></div><div class="main-content">

                    <div class="section active" id="introduction">
                        <div class="section-header"><h3>INTRODUCTION</h3></div>
                        <div class="section-content"><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>WELCOME TO THIS MODULE</h4><div><p><b>Understanding Unconscious Bias at Work</b></p><p>This module is designed to help you recognise and understand unconscious bias – what it is, how it shows up in the workplace, and why it matters for inclusive leadership.</p><p>By the end of this module, you will be able to identify common types of bias and understand how they can influence everyday workplace decisions.</p></div></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="text-content-render"><p><b>What you will learn:</b></p><ul><li>What unconscious bias is and why everyone has it</li><li>Five common types of workplace bias</li><li>How bias can affect recruitment, performance reviews, and team dynamics</li><li>Practical ways to recognise and counter bias in your leadership</li></ul><p><b>Why this matters:</b></p><p>As a leader, your decisions affect your team every day – who gets opportunities, who gets heard, and who feels valued. Understanding your own biases is the first step to making fairer, more inclusive decisions.</p></div></div><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>A NOTE BEFORE WE BEGIN</h4><div><p>Having unconscious biases does not make you a bad person. <b>Everyone has them</b> – they are a natural part of how our brains work.</p><p>The goal of this module is not to make you feel guilty, but to help you become more aware. Awareness is the first step to change.</p></div></div></div></div>
