                        <div class="section-header"><h3>SUMMARY & REFLECTION</h3></div>
                        <div class="section-content"><div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>KEY TAKEAWAYS</h4><div><p><b>What you have learned in this module:</b></p><ul><li><b>Unconscious bias</b> = automatic mental shortcuts that influence our judgements without us realising</li><li>Everyone has biases – they are a normal part of how our brains work</li><li>Bias is often <b>unintentional</b> and can conflict with our conscious values</li><li>Common workplace biases include: <b>affinity bias, confirmation bias, gender bias, age bias, and the halo effect</b></li><li>Bias affects real decisions: hiring, promotions, feedback, and daily interactions</li><li>Small biased decisions accumulate over time, creating significant unfairness</li><li><b>Awareness is the first step</b> – once we recognise bias, we can take action to counter it</li></ul></div></div></div>

<div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="key-definition-box"><h4>FIVE ACTIONS FOR INCLUSIVE LEADERS</h4><div><ol><li><b>Slow down</b> – Give yourself time to think before making quick judgements about people</li><li><b>Use structure</b> – Consistent criteria and processes reduce the space for bias to operate</li><li><b>Seek evidence</b> – Challenge your assumptions by looking for facts, not just feelings</li><li><b>Include others</b> – Diverse perspectives help spot blind spots you cannot see alone</li><li><b>Stay curious</b> – Keep learning about bias and reflecting on your own patterns</li></ol></div></div></div>

<div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="feedback-box-render"><h4>Reflection: Your Personal Commitment</h4><p>Think about your own workplace and your role as a leader (or future leader).</p><p><b>Which type of bias do you think you need to be most aware of in your own decision-making?</b></p><p>Consider: Which of the five biases (affinity, confirmation, gender, age, halo effect) might be most relevant to decisions you make regularly?</p><textarea placeholder="Write your reflection here..."></textarea></div></div>

<div class="section-content-wrapper"><div class="feedback-box-render"><h4>One Action You Will Take</h4><p><b>What is ONE specific thing you will do differently to reduce the impact of bias in your workplace?</b></p><p>Think about a concrete action you can take in the next week – it could be in how you run meetings, give feedback, or make decisions about opportunities.</p><textarea placeholder="Write your commitment here..."></textarea></div></div>

